{
  "id": "019d331e-2e27-71e0-ad95-8008d1c1b352",
  "content": "# Multi-Spoke Workspace Design (2026-03-28)\n\n## Concept\nMultiple Claude Code instances (spokes) in separate containers, all connected to one shared corvia server (hub). Knowledge pools in real-time via MCP. Each spoke runs dev-loop on a separate issue/branch.\n\n## Key Decisions (Pending Approval)\n- **Auth**: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY env var for spokes (no manual login). Mounted credentials as fallback.\n- **Coordination**: Knowledge-based (corvia_write + corvia_search), not process-based messaging. Episodic memory pattern.\n- **Two registries clarified**: Claude Code has ephemeral process registry (teams). corvia has permanent knowledge registry (agents). Different layers, not competing.\n- **Dashboard**: Spoke visibility via MCP heartbeat (corvia_agent_status), not filesystem session watching.\n- **Workspace as product**: corvia workspace spoke create/list/destroy. Server bind 0.0.0.0. Spoke templates.\n- **Term \"spoke\" adopted** for worker containers.\n- **Bridging**: Independent Claude Code instances + shared corvia = functional multi-agent without network teams. When Claude Code ships network teams, corvia is already the MCP backend.\n\n## Doc: docs/decisions/2026-03-28-multi-spoke-workspace-brainstorm.md",
